      "text": [
        " \"إِنَّمَا تَأْكُلُهُ اَلسِّبَاعُ\" \" قَالَ حَرِيزٌ يَعْنِي حَتَّى تُغَيِّرَهُ اَلشَّمْسُ أَوِ اَلنَّارُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4232 - Hariz narrated from Zurara, from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) that the Messenger of Allah (swt) prohibited eating meat raw, meaning uncooked.\nThe Prophet (sw) said: \"It is only eaten by wild beasts.\"\nHariz said: \"This means until it is altered by the sun or fire.\""
        ]
      }
    },
